{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is the vision model’s real classification judgment on explicit content plus downstream hold action. A stubbed classifier can force \"flagged\" and hide misclassification failures. System-only infra is insufficient because correctness depends on model output content. Workflow is rejected because this behavior is a single model decision, not multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Submit a curated set of real explicit images to the production-like moderation path using the real vision model, then assert each is marked flagged and routed to human-review hold (never published).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is model robustness/quality against adversarial text variants; deterministic mocks always pass and miss real classifier failures. Integration is too low because the key risk is not module wiring but real model behavior under obfuscation. Workflow is rejected because only one agentic classification decision is under test.","test_description":"Send a corpus of hate-speech phrases with obfuscations (leet substitutions, homoglyphs, mixed unicode) through the real text moderation model and assert they are flagged and held.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior text focuses on orchestration/state handoff: after both checks pass, publish must occur and not be dropped. This can be caught with in-process wiring using deterministic pass responses from both classifiers. Higher levels rejected by behavior text: it does not ask to validate classifier quality, only that a \"post that passes both content checks\" is published.","test_description":"Wire moderation service + queue/repo/publisher modules with fake classifier adapters returning PASS for image/text, then assert final state is published and no hold/drop path is taken.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires an end-to-end pipeline with multiple model-backed stages (`image check, text check, publish decision`) and a single SLA across the sequence. Mocks hide queueing, cross-stage latency accumulation, and real model/API variance under load. System alone is insufficient because the requirement is on the chained moderation workflow, not one infrastructure boundary.","test_description":"Run end-to-end submissions through the real moderation path with real image and text model calls during peak-like load; measure submit-to-final-decision latency and assert p95 (or specified percentile) is <= 5s for the complete pipeline.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.24,"Workflow":0.45}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure mode depends on real unavailability signals (timeouts, connection errors, 5xx, DNS/TLS/socket behavior) from an external model service. In-process mocks may not reproduce transport/SDK error semantics and can hide auto-approve regressions. Agentic is rejected because output quality/content is irrelevant; this is outage handling.","test_description":"Induce real vision-service unavailability in a staging-like environment (e.g., block endpoint or force timeouts) and assert image posts enter retry queue with no publish/auto-approve path taken.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real vision-model behavior on borderline inputs across repeated calls; stubs cannot expose decision instability. Integration is too low because the risk is model-output consistency, not just state plumbing. Workflow is rejected because this is repeated evaluation of one agentic decision type, not a multi-stage agent pipeline handoff.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly within the target window through the real vision moderation path and assert decision consistency rate meets policy (or cache-stabilized consistency if designed).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.08}}]}
